  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Pool (Zhang et al. 2020) fuses the topological structure and feature information of the graph to score the nodes.",
    "TAP (Gao et al. 2021a) employs a twostage voting process to select important nodes in the graph, where local voting scores nodes based on their similarity to their neighboring nodes, and global voting scores nodes globally on their importance on the whole graph.",
    "RepPool (Li et al. 2020b) evaluates the value of nodes by combining global and representative scores and uses a greedy algorithm to select important and representative nodes.",
    "This approach preserves key information and structure in the graph, enabling better utilization of this information in subsequent graph convolutional layers.",
    "Pool (Ma et al. 2020) selects nodes that occupy important positions in the graph and are tightly connected to other nodes as nodes in the pooled graph by using the concepts of path scoring and maximum entropy random wandering."
  ],
